item.description:
I am a Financial Economist at the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). Ideas and views are my own and do not reflect the views of the SEC or the U.S. government.

Prior to this, I was a postdoctoral research fellow at the Criminal Justice Administrative Records System (CJARS) at the University of Michigan. I received my Ph.D. in Economics from the University of Houston in 2020.

My last name rhymes with “who”
